'Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safer, thanks to the progress made in combating terrorism,' he says.
The government continues to rehabilitate areas that have been destroyed by terrorists and to normalize the situation on the ground.
All circumstances now exist for the voluntary return of refugees to the country they have had to leave because of terrorism and the unilateral economic measures that threaten their daily lives and existence.
The UN estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have fled their country since the war began in 2011.
It is estimated that there are still about six million people living in the country who need humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said that the Syrian regime would welcome help to restore the devastated country.
However, he stressed that Syria would not accept conditional assistance or assistance from countries that had subsidized the uprising.
